Commitment-to-Removing-Reserved-Profiles: Commitment to Removing Reserved Profiles Upon Request
The initial developers of the DeSo blockchain reserved a subset of Twitter users' profiles early on in order to prevent squatting and impersonation

This being said, any user with a reserved profile who would like to have their profile removed from bitclout.com can request this removal by messaging the @deso handle on Twitter. This is needed in order to authenticate the owner of the Twitter handle corresponding to the reserved profile. bitclout.com agrees to remove the reserved profile of any user who messages @deso with the corresponding Twitter account
